					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Game maker should work well enough for prototyping games. You can set up and blend frame buffers as much as you’d like. But it really depends on what you want to achieve. A perfect emulation of the whole NES featureset sounds cumbersome, for example. It should work well to test graphics and physics but that’s about it.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
